# Claude Code Caracal Policy Playbook

This folder is a copy-paste Claude Code setup for designing, authoring, reviewing, debugging, and maintaining Caracal policy data documents.

## Use it for

- discovering policy requirements before authoring data
- comparing policy data approaches and tradeoffs before implementation
- validating that data documents match the platform contract's shapes
- writing `app_ids`, `grants`, `confinement`, and `restrict` data documents
- reviewing existing data documents
- explaining policy behavior in plain language
- debugging denied or confusing policy behavior with validation and simulation inputs
- planning validation, simulation, policy-set activation, audit review, and rollback

## Install

Copy `CLAUDE.md` and `.claude/` into the repository where users want Claude Code to help author policies.

## Behavior

Claude should:

- understand the requirement before authoring data
- suggest the simplest safe policy data shape before generating Rego
- use Caracal docs and OPA docs before assumptions
- use `package caracal.authz`, `import rego.v1`, and the `# caracal:data-document` directive
- author only `app_ids`, `grants`, `confinement`, and `restrict` data, never a `result` rule
- distinguish grants from data documents
- explain tradeoffs between grants, confinement, and restriction overlays when more than one design is possible
- recommend safer or thinner workarounds when the desired behavior is not directly supported
- provide a suggested GitHub issue write-up when functionality is missing from Caracal policy support
- keep examples limited to app, resource, scope, role, confinement, and restriction data
- never expose secrets or real customer identifiers

## Not for

- SDK integration
- provider dashboard mapping
- creating grants, resources, applications, tokens, clients, or API keys

If a requested policy behavior is unsupported or cannot be verified safely, direct the user to [the Caracal issue form](https://github.com/Garudex-Labs/caracal/issues/new/choose) and provide a short suggested write-up they can submit.
